BIB                 13         27
TITLE      The day-one experiment at SLEGS: systematic
            measurement of the (g,1n) cross sections on 197Au and
            159Tb for resolving existing data discrepancies
AUTHOR     (Zirui Hao, Gongtao Fan, Hongwei Wang, Longxiang Liu,
            Hanghua Xu, Yue Zhang, Yuxuan Yang, Sheng Jin,
            Kaijie Chen, Zhicai Li, Pu Jiao, Qiankun Sun,
            Mengdie Zhou, Shan Ye, Zhenwei Wang, Wenqing Shen,
            Yugang Ma)
REFERENCE  (J,CSB,70,2591,2025)
INSTITUTE  (3CPRARI,3CPRNRS,3CPRUCA,3CPRFUD)
FACILITY   (ESTRG,3CPRARI) 3.5 GeV storage ring of Shanghai Laser
            Electron Gamma Source (SLEGS)
INC-SOURCE (LCS) CO2 laser photons scattered by 3.5 GeV electrons
SAMPLE     10 mm in diameter x 4 mm
DETECTOR   (HE3SP) 3He flat efficiency detector (FED)
           (BGO) for gamma spectrum measurement
METHOD     (RINGR) for neutron detection efficiency determination
ANALYSIS   (UNFLD) unfolding with LCS photon energy profile
            measured by the BGO detector
REL-REF    (M,K2613001,T.Renstroom+,J,PR/C,98,054310,2018)
            Unfolding method
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
           (ERR-1) Systematic uncertainty
           (ERR-2) Theoretical uncertainty
HISTORY    (20251126R) Wang Jimin. Received from Zirui Hao.
           (20251126C) On
ENDBIB              27
NOCOMMON             0          0
